{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Small Ocean"], "type": "title", "extent": [39, 55], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [55, 142], "text": ["Creates a small patch of ocean complete with a material and depth information."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [142, 487], "text": ["This tool is useful for creating an ocean like surface. However, it is not a simulation, it is a deformer that does not use DOPs at all. You can scrub through the timeline and watch the ocean evolve without any simulation.  For a simulated ocean, use the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/wave_tank", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SHELF/wave_tank"}, {"text": ["Wave Tank"], "fullpath": "/shelf/wavetank", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/wavetank"}, " tool on ", {"text": ["Particle Fluids"], "type": "ui"}, " shelf tab."]}, {"body": [{"body": [], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "attrs": {"src": "/videos/OceanSurfaceWW.mp4"}, "extent": [487, 495], "container": true, "type": "video"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "video_group"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [561, 647], "text": ["In the Oceans shelf tab, click ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/oceanwaves", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SHELF/oceanwaves"}, " Small Ocean."]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [647, 990], "text": ["The tool will create and wire the ", {"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}, " and ", {"text": ["Ocean Evaluate"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate"}, " nodes necessary to control the shape and movement of the ocean. It will also create an ", {"text": ["Ocean Surface shader"], "fullpath": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface"}, " and attach it to the newly created ", {"text": ["ocean_surface"], "type": "code"}, " object."]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [990, 1292], "text": ["The animation is driven by the ", {"text": ["Time"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter on the ", {"text": ["Ocean Evaluate"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate"}, " node. The default expression is ", {"text": ["$T"], "type": "code"}, " (the current time). You can edit this expression to change the animation direction and speed (for example, ", {"text": ["$T * 2"], "type": "code"}, " to make the ocean move twice as fast)."]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1292, 1338], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/oceanwave.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/oceanwave.png"}]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [1351, 1488], "text": ["Change your ", {"text": ["shading mode"], "fullpath": "/basics/view", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/basics/view"}, " to ", {"text": ["Smooth Shaded Mode"], "type": "ui"}, " to get a better view of the deforming ocean surface."]}], "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [1338, 1351], "container": true, "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1488, 1703], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["ocean_preview"], "type": "code"}, " node is used to preview your ocean surface in the viewport. The ", {"text": ["ocean_render"], "type": "code"}, " node is used by the ", {"text": ["Ocean Surface shader"], "fullpath": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface"}, " at render time. "]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1703, 2195], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}, " node has all of the tools for changing the look of your ocean. For example, on the ", {"text": ["Wind"], "type": "ui"}, " tab, the ", {"text": ["Speed"], "type": "ui"}, " will affect the amplitude of the waves, the ", {"text": ["Directional Bias"], "type": "ui"}, " lets you create waves that move more or less in one direction, and the ", {"text": ["Chop"], "type": "ui"}, " which allows you to create the sharp peaks on the waves. The ", {"text": ["Wave Amplitude"], "type": "ui"}, " tab also has some very useful parameters, such as the ", {"text": ["Scale"], "type": "ui"}, " which controls the size of the waves."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Small Ocean"], "extent": [537, 561], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [2813, 3013], "text": ["It is important to remember to use the ", {"text": ["Reset Simulation"], "type": "ui"}, " button on the ", {"text": ["ocean_render"], "type": "code"}, " node to make sure your ocean preview and ocean render nodes are synchronized."]}], "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [2799, 2813], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["For rendering, this tool creates a ", {"text": ["fetch node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/out/fetch", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/out/fetch"}, " at the output level which is connected to the compositing network inside of the ", {"text": ["ocean_render"], "type": "code"}, " node. If you would like to generate displacement maps at render-time, you can connect this node to the input of a ", {"text": ["Mantra"], "fullpath": "/nodes/out/ifd", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/out/ifd"}, " node. If you use the ", {"text": ["Render"], "type": "ui"}, " button on this ", {"text": ["Mantra"], "fullpath": "/nodes/out/ifd", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/out/ifd"}, " node, you will cause the ", {"text": ["Ocean Evaluate"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate"}, " node to generate the texture maps required by the ", {"text": ["Ocean Surface shader"], "fullpath": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface"}, " for the specific frame you are viewing. "], "extent": [2206, 2799], "container": true, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3150, 3240], "text": ["Spectrum geometry will have to be re-generated if you alter the wave parameters."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [3140, 3150], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["To generate spectrum geometry, click the ", {"text": ["Save to Disk"], "type": "ui"}, " button on the ", {"text": ["save_spectra"], "type": "code"}, " node in the ", {"text": ["ocean surface"], "type": "code"}, " network."], "extent": [3013, 3140], "container": true, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet"}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3240, 3672], "text": ["A velocity attribute is added to the ocean surface to allow the use of motion-blur at render-time. This information is stored on the points of your input grid. If you feel that the motion-blur is not accurate enough, you can change the rows and columns on your grid to increase the number of points. Keep in mind that drastically increasing the point count on your grid could negatively affect the speed of your renders."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3672, 4092], "text": ["If it is important for your scene to have information below your ocean surface, you can still optimize your renders by adjusting the ", {"text": ["Volume Step Rate"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Volume Shadow Step Rate"], "type": "ui"}, " settings on the ", {"text": ["Sampling"], "type": "ui"}, " tab of the ", {"text": ["Mantra"], "fullpath": "/nodes/out/ifd", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/out/ifd"}, " node. Often the volumetric element of the ocean is used for a general sub-surface scattering and attenuation effect and does not necessarily need to be highly detailed."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4092, 4383], "text": ["If the space below your ocean surface is not important in your final image, you could disable refraction on the ", {"text": ["Ocean Surface shader"], "fullpath": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface"}, " and turn off visibility on the ", {"text": ["ocean_interior"], "type": "code"}, " object. This will reduce the length of your render significantly."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4383, 4559], "text": ["Lowering the ", {"text": ["Frequency"], "type": "ui"}, " on ", {"text": ["Ocean Surface shader"], "fullpath": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/gallery/shop/vopmaterial/oceansurface"}, " > ", {"text": ["Foam"], "type": "ui"}, " > ", {"text": ["Streaks"], "type": "ui"}, " subtab will create a more broken up effect of the foam."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [106, 263], "text": ["Navigate to the ", {"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}, " node and adjust the ", {"text": ["Wave Scale"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter on the ", {"text": ["Wave Amplitude"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [263, 369], "text": ["This value is multiplied by the ", {"text": ["Speed"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter on the ", {"text": ["Wind"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [391, 453], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_height_low.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_height_low.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [369, 391], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [475, 555], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_height_high.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_height_high.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [453, 475], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "col_group"}], "container": true, "text": [" Set the height of the wave"], "role": "item", "extent": [62, 106], "indent": 8, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [602, 755], "text": ["Navigate to the ", {"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}, " node and adjust the ", {"text": ["Directional Bias"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter on the ", {"text": ["Wind"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [755, 1000], "text": ["This controls how many frequencies are moving in the same direction as the wind. Increasing this value will cause more frequencies to travel in the same direction, which is useful for creating shoreline effects."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [1000, 1226], "text": ["You can also try increasing the ", {"text": ["Directional Movement"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter. This will dampen the waves moving in the opposite direction of the wind, leaving only the ones moving in the same direction."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [1248, 1310], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_direction1.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_direction1.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [1226, 1248], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [1332, 1402], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_direction.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_direction.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [1310, 1332], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "col_group"}], "container": true, "text": [" Set the direction of the waves"], "role": "item", "extent": [555, 602], "indent": 8, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [1449, 1598], "text": ["Navigate to the ", {"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}, " node and adjust the ", {"text": ["Chop"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter on the ", {"text": ["Wind"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [1598, 1755], "text": ["Increasing this parameter creates sharp peaks on waves. However, if this value is too high waves, may invert on themselves."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [1777, 1837], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_peak_low.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_peak_low.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [1755, 1777], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [1859, 1937], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_peak_high.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_peak_high.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [1837, 1859], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "col_group"}], "container": true, "text": [" Control the height of the peak"], "role": "item", "extent": [1402, 1449], "indent": 8, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "extent": [1983, 2116], "text": ["Increase the ", {"text": ["Resolution Exponent"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter on the ", {"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}, " node."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 24, "extent": [2138, 2342], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["Resolution Exponent"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter will not only determine the quality of your ocean, but also the size of the texture maps that you will eventually write out."]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [2116, 2138], "indent": 16, "type": "note"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [2365, 2425], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_regular.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_regular.png"}, " "]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [2342, 2365], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 20, "extent": [2448, 2525], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/wave_detailed.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/wave_detailed.png"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item", "extent": [2425, 2448], "indent": 16, "type": "col"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "col_group"}], "container": true, "text": [" Add more detail to your ocean"], "role": "item", "extent": [1937, 1983], "indent": 8, "type": "task"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "extent": [2562, 2635], "text": ["Use the ", {"text": ["Large Ocean"], "fullpath": "/shelf/largeocean", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/largeocean"}, " shelf tool."]}], "container": true, "text": [" Create a large ocean"], "role": "item", "extent": [2525, 2562], "indent": 8, "type": "task"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "task_group"}], "container": true, "level": 3, "text": ["Changing the look of your ocean"], "extent": [16, 62], "indent": 0, "type": "h", "id": "howto"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [2195, 2206], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4603, 4649], "text": [{"text": ["Ocean Spectrum"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanspectrum"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4649, 4695], "text": [{"text": ["Ocean Evaluate"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanevaluate"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4695, 4733], "text": [{"text": ["Ocean Foam"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/oceanfoam", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/oceanfoam"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [4594, 4603], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["Small Ocean"], "summary": ["Creates a small patch of ocean complete with a material and depth information."], "attrs": {"tags": "oceans", "icon": "SHELF/oceanwaves"}, "included": ["/shelf/common_ocean"], "type": "root"}